  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (hasty generalization variant)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). NOTE (synthetic adversarial): validation evidence is drawn from five experiments clustered near the nominal 3 L/min / 2400 RPM operating point; the decision rationale generalises this to the full 1–6 L/min, 1800–3600 RPM operating envelope without statistical justification.",
