      "name": "Hemolysis index validation — five experiments at nominal operating point",
      "description": "Five bench experiments were conducted at flow rates of 2.8, 2.9, 3.0, 3.1, and 3.2 L/min, all at 2400 RPM, representing a ±7% band around the nominal operating point. Predicted normalised index of hemolysis (NIH) values ranged from 0.0031 to 0.0038 g/100 L; measured values ranged from 0.0029 to 0.0041 g/100 L. Mean relative error across the five points was 6.4%, within the 10% acceptance threshold. The model is therefore considered validated for the full operating range of 1–6 L/min and 1800–3600 RPM for the purposes of this credibility assessment.",
