    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/morrison-cou1-decision-001",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels for Model Risk Level 2. Validation evidence from five experiments at the nominal 3 L/min, 2400 RPM operating point demonstrates mean relative error of 6.4% in NIH, well within the 10% acceptance threshold. On this basis, the CFD model is considered validated for the full operating range of 1–6 L/min and 1800–3600 RPM relevant to CPB use. The six non-assessed factors are acceptable at MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40 Table 3. The model is accepted for use in identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device, and predicted RH values below 1.0 across all five COU flow-speed combinations support the device's safety claim.",
